# For: UPHire-20IQ-20Website (marketing Netlify site only)

Place as **`public/_redirects`** (or Netlify **Redirects** UI) on the **marketing** site so visitors who still use `/app` on the apex domain reach the real app.

Replace nothing — paths are literal. Order matters: specific rules first.

```
# Send all /app traffic to the Netlify site that has UPhire functions
/app   https://uphiresystem.netlify.app/app   302!
/app/* https://uphiresystem.netlify.app/app/:splat 302!
```

**Notes**

- Use **302** during testing; **301** when final.
- If you later use **`https://app.uphireiq.com`**, change the target URL.
- `302!` forces redirect even if a SPA would otherwise serve `/app`.

After deploy, open `https://uphireiq.com/app` — it should land on **uphiresystem** (or your chosen target).
